         <abstract>
            <p>The practitioner attitude toward all academic finance associations, and particularly toward the FMA and its journal, is the subject of this essay. Its author finds that, based on some progress to date, the FMA should be able to build better bridges between academician and practitioner. He feels the journal still falls short of being able to make a contribution to the managerial sector because of the character and presentation of its papers.</p>
